{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":607,"text":"So I was trained to become a gymnast"},{"time":3319,"text":"for two years in Hunan, China in the 1970s."},{"time":6975,"text":"When I was in the first grade, the government"},{"time":9520,"text":"wanted to transfer me to a school for athletes,"},{"time":12127,"text":"all expenses paid."},{"time":14175,"text":"But my tiger mother said, \"No.\""},{"time":16823,"text":"My parents wanted me to become"},{"time":18959,"text":"an engineer like them."},{"time":21063,"text":"After surviving the Cultural Revolution,"},{"time":23150,"text":"they firmly believed there's only one sure way to happiness:"},{"time":26959,"text":"a safe and well-paid job."},{"time":29892,"text":"It is not important if I like the job or not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32687,"text":"But my dream was to become a Chinese opera singer."},{"time":37967,"text":"That is me playing my imaginary piano."},{"time":41615,"text":"An opera singer must start training young"},{"time":43799,"text":"to learn acrobatics,"},{"time":45383,"text":"so I tried everything I could to go to opera school."},{"time":48327,"text":"I even wrote to the school principal"},{"time":50594,"text":"and the host of a radio show."},{"time":53355,"text":"But no adults liked the idea."},{"time":57161,"text":"No adults believed I was serious."},{"time":59884,"text":"Only my friends supported me, but they were kids,"},{"time":63128,"text":"just as powerless as I was."},{"time":65884,"text":"So at age 15, I knew I was too old to be trained."},{"time":71649,"text":"My dream would never come true."},{"time":74616,"text":"I was afraid that for the rest of my life"},{"time":77924,"text":"some second-class happiness"},{"time":79961,"text":"would be the best I could hope for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82498,"text":"But that's so unfair."},{"time":84926,"text":"So I was determined to find another calling."},{"time":88728,"text":"Nobody around to teach me? Fine."},{"time":91465,"text":"I turned to books."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93697,"text":"I satisfied my hunger for parental advice"},{"time":97339,"text":"from this book by a family of writers and musicians.[\"Correspondence in the Family of Fou Lei\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":102216,"text":"I found my role model of an independent woman"},{"time":105289,"text":"when Confucian tradition requires obedience.[\"Jane Eyre\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":109133,"text":"And I learned to be efficient from this book.[\"Cheaper by the Dozen\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":112830,"text":"And I was inspired to study abroad after reading these."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116795,"text":"[\"Complete Works of Sanmao\" (aka Echo Chan)] [\"Lessons From History\" by Nan Huaijin]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":118866,"text":"I came to the U.S. in 1995,"},{"time":122057,"text":"so which books did I read here first?"},{"time":124938,"text":"Books banned in China, of course."},{"time":128463,"text":"\"The Good Earth\" is about Chinese peasant life."},{"time":132133,"text":"That's just not convenient for propaganda. Got it."},{"time":136235,"text":"The Bible is interesting, but strange."},{"time":139960,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":142445,"text":"That's a topic for a different day."},{"time":145916,"text":"But the fifth commandment gave me an epiphany:"},{"time":149211,"text":"\"You shall honor your father and mother.\""},{"time":152190,"text":"\"Honor,\" I said. \"That's so different,"},{"time":155140,"text":"and better, than obey.\""},{"time":156879,"text":"So it becomes my tool to climb out"},{"time":159383,"text":"of this Confucian guilt trap"},{"time":161499,"text":"and to restart my relationship with my parents."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165771,"text":"Encountering a new culture also started my habit"},{"time":168793,"text":"of comparative reading."},{"time":170565,"text":"It offers many insights."},{"time":172420,"text":"For example, I found this map out of place at first"},{"time":177200,"text":"because this is what Chinese students grew up with."},{"time":182085,"text":"It had never occurred to me,"},{"time":183586,"text":"China doesn't have to be at the center of the world."},{"time":186721,"text":"A map actually carries somebody's view."},{"time":190974,"text":"Comparative reading actually is nothing new."},{"time":193382,"text":"It's a standard practice in the academic world."},{"time":196686,"text":"There are even research fields"},{"time":198154,"text":"such as comparative religion and comparative literature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202099,"text":"Compare and contrast gives scholars"},{"time":204334,"text":"a more complete understanding of a topic."},{"time":207340,"text":"So I thought, well, if comparative reading"},{"time":209093,"text":"works for research, why not do it in daily life too?"},{"time":212929,"text":"So I started reading books in pairs."},{"time":216304,"text":"So they can be about people --"},{"time":217518,"text":"[\"Benjamin Franklin\" by Walter Isaacson][\"John Adams\" by David McCullough] --"},{"time":218401,"text":"who are involved in the same event,"},{"time":220909,"text":"or friends with shared experiences."},{"time":223588,"text":"[\"Personal History\" by Katharine Graham][\"The Snowball: Warren Buffett and the Business of Life,\" by Alice Schroeder]"},{"time":224988,"text":"I also compare the same stories in different genres -- (Laughter)"},{"time":229386,"text":"[Holy Bible: King James Version][\"Lamb\" by Chrisopher Moore] --"},{"time":231498,"text":"or similar stories from different cultures,"},{"time":234635,"text":"as Joseph Campbell did in his wonderful book.[\"The Power of Myth\" by Joseph Campbell]"},{"time":237516,"text":"For example, both the Christ and the Buddha"},{"time":240909,"text":"went through three temptations."},{"time":243342,"text":"For the Christ, the temptations"},{"time":245144,"text":"are economic, political and spiritual."},{"time":249119,"text":"For the Buddha, they are all psychological:"},{"time":253445,"text":"lust, fear and social duty -- interesting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260763,"text":"So if you know a foreign language, it's also fun"},{"time":263802,"text":"to read your favorite books in two languages."},{"time":265699,"text":"[\"The Way of Chuang Tzu\" Thomas Merton][\"Tao: The Watercourse Way\" Alan Watts]"},{"time":266951,"text":"Instead of lost in translation, I found there is much to gain."},{"time":270527,"text":"For example, it's through translation that I realized"},{"time":274735,"text":"\"happiness\" in Chinese literally means \"fast joy.\" Huh!"},{"time":280708,"text":"\"Bride\" in Chinese literally means \"new mother.\" Uh-oh."},{"time":285997,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":289258,"text":"Books have given me a magic portal to connect with people"},{"time":294645,"text":"of the past and the present."},{"time":297290,"text":"I know I shall never feel lonely or powerless again."},{"time":301525,"text":"Having a dream shattered really is nothing"},{"time":304202,"text":"compared to what many others have suffered."},{"time":307138,"text":"I have come to believe that coming true"},{"time":309866,"text":"is not the only purpose of a dream."},{"time":313146,"text":"Its most important purpose is to get us in touch"},{"time":317047,"text":"with where dreams come from,"},{"time":319162,"text":"where passion comes from, where happiness comes from."},{"time":322066,"text":"Even a shattered dream can do that for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326288,"text":"So because of books, I'm here today,"},{"time":328542,"text":"happy, living again with a purpose and a clarity,"},{"time":332202,"text":"most of the time."},{"time":333952,"text":"So may books be always with you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337513,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338991,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":340839,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":344484,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}